pefucaldinum, Hierosolymitanum, PMLb, La und Lc rekonstruieren lässt. Diese Florilegien überliefern 2906 Texte der zweiten Rezension, die dem Alten und Neuen Testament, den Kirchenvätern, Philon von Alexandria und Flavius Josephus entnommen sind.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Sep 2018)1 aDeclerck, José, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2018z9783110603248oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311055580640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110556711423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110556711.jpg  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017